 

1. Constant:- It does not depends on the time. It is a constant time operation. 


2. Linear 0(n):- If the Array size increases then time increases accoringly. 


3. Quadratic 0(n2):-  Quadratic time complexity happens when the number of operations grows proportional to the square of the input size. 


4. Logarithmic 0(log n):-   Logarithmic complexity happens when the problem size is reduced by a fixed fraction in every step. 

 
5. N (logn):- This complexity is a combination of: 

Linear → O(n)  and  Logarithmic → O(log n)  

f(n)=n logn 

It is faster than O(n²) and is considered very efficient for large datasets. 

 
6. Exponential :- It is the opposite if the Logarithmic. Exponential complexity happens when the number of operations doubles with every additional input. 

It grows extremely fast. 

 

 

 
